-- Ecuador’s Correa Names New Defense and Agriculture Ministers
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-04-18T18:09:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/ecuador-s-correa-names-new-defense-and-agriculture-ministers.html
Ecuador’s President  Rafael Correa 
appointed Miguel Carvajal as the South American country’s new
defense minister and Javier Ponce as agriculture minister.  Carvajal, who previously served as the vice minister of
agriculture, is replacing Ponce who will in turn move to the
Agriculture Ministry after the former chief, Wilfrido Staynley Vera, resigned in February, according to a statement published
today in the president’s official gazette.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 